## 🛠️ Qox Developer Environment Setup
Use this notebook to authenticate and install the **private** `develop` branch of the `qox` library.

> **Prerequisite:** Ensure you have a Personal Access Token (PAT) saved in the **Secrets (Key icon)** on the left sidebar as `GH_TOKEN` and that **"Notebook access"** is toggled **ON**.

---

```python
#@title ⚡ Click Play to Initialize Dev Environment { display-mode: "form" }
import os
from google.colab import userdata

def setup_dev_env():
    try:
        # 1. Retrieve the Secret
        token = userdata.get('GH_TOKEN')
        print("🔑 Token retrieved successfully...")

        # 2. Install Build Dependencies
        print("📦 Installing maturin (Rust build backend)...")
        os.system("pip install maturin -q")

        # 3. Install Private Bindings
        print("🚀 Cloning and installing qox-python (develop branch)...")

        # Define the URL with the specific subdirectory
        repo_url = f"git+https://{token}@[github.com/bboutelje/qox.git@develop#subdirectory=qox-python](https://github.com/bboutelje/qox.git@develop#subdirectory=qox-python)"

        # Using ! to show real-time progress during the Rust build
        !pip install {repo_url}

        import qox
        print("\n✅ SUCCESS: Development environment is active.")

    except Exception as e:
        print("\n❌ ERROR: Setup Failed")
        print(f"Details: {e}")
        print("\nHELP: Check that your 'GH_TOKEN' is correct and authorized in the Secrets tab.")

setup_dev_env()
